data.reasoningText:
Now I have a good understanding of the project. Let me plan the component decomposition and then implement it.

## Component Plan: Kanban Board

### Component Tree
```
Board                    (page — owns task list, search state, loading/error)
├── BoardStats           (read-only summary stats bar)
├── BoardSearchBar       (search input, owns search text)
└── BoardColumn          (one per status: To Do, In Progress, Done)
    ├── TaskCard         (displays a single task with move buttons)
    └── AddTaskForm      (inline form to add a task to this column)


```

The Board component will manage the task list, search text, and loading states, passing filtered tasks down to each column based on status. Each column receives its tasks and callbacks for moving items left or right, while the search bar and stats bar get their own data and event handlers. I'll build the leaf components first—TaskCard, AddTaskForm, and BoardStats—then work up to the container components.

For the folder structure, I'm settling on putting the sub-components in Components/Board/ and the main page at Components/Pages/Board.razor to keep things organized.

```

razor
@page "/board"
@using Components.Board
@inject NavigationManager Navigation

<PageTitle>Board</PageTitle>

<div class="board-container">
    <h1>Task Board</h1>
    <div class="board">
        @foreach (var column in columns)
        {
            <BoardColumn Column="column" OnTaskAdded="HandleTaskAdded" OnTaskRemoved="HandleTaskRemoved" />
        }
    </div>
</div>

@code {
    private List<BoardColumnData> columns = new();

    protected override void OnInitialized()
    {
        columns = new()
        {
            new() { Title = "To Do", Tasks = new() },
            new() { Title = "In Progress", Tasks = new() },
            new() { Title = "Done", Tasks = new() }
        };
    }

    private void HandleTaskAdded(string columnTitle, string taskTitle)
    {
        var column = columns.FirstOrDefault(c => c.Title == columnTitle);
        if (column != null)
        {
            column.Tasks.Add(new() { Title = taskTitle });
        }
    }

    private void HandleTaskRemoved(string columnTitle, string taskId)
    {
        var column = columns.FirstOrDefault(c => c.Title == columnTitle);
        if (column != null)
        {
            column.Tasks.RemoveAll(t => t.Id == taskId);
        }
    }
}
```

Now I'll create the BoardColumn component that manages a single column with its tasks and the form to add new ones.

```razor
@using Components.Board

<div class="board-column">
    <h2>@Column.Title</h2>
    <div class="tasks">
        @foreach (var task in Column.Tasks)
        {
            <TaskCard Task="task" OnRemove="() => HandleRemove(task.Id)" />
        }
    </div>
    <AddTaskForm OnSubmit="HandleAddTask" />
</div>

@code {
    [Parameter]
    public BoardColumnData Column { get; set; }

    [Parameter]
    public EventCallback<(string, string)> OnTaskAdded { get; set; }

    [Parameter]
    public EventCallback<(string, string)> OnTaskRemoved { get; set; }

    private async Task HandleAddTask(string taskTitle)
    {
        await OnTaskAdded.InvokeAsync((Column.Title, taskTitle));
    }

    private async Task HandleRemove(string taskId)
    {
        await OnTaskRemoved.InvokeAsync((Column.Title, taskId));
    }
}
```

Now the TaskCard component to display individual tasks.

```razor
<div class="task-card">
    <p>@Task.Title</p>
    <button @onclick="OnRemove">Delete</button>
</div>

@code {
    [Parameter]
    public TaskData Task { get; set; }

    [Parameter]
    public EventCallback OnRemove { get; set; }
}
```

And the AddTaskForm component for adding new tasks.

```razor
<form @onsubmit="HandleSubmit">
    <input type="text" @bind="taskTitle" placeholder="Add a new task..." />
    <button type="submit">Add</button>
</form>

@code {
    private string taskTitle = "";

    [Parameter]
    public EventCallback<string> OnSubmit { get; set; }

    private async Task HandleSubmit()
    {
        if (!string.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(taskTitle))
        {
            await OnSubmit.InvokeAsync(taskTitle);
            taskTitle = "";
        }
    }
}
```

Finally, I'll create the data models to support these components.

```csharp
public class BoardColumnData
{
    public string Title { get; set; }
    public List<TaskData> Tasks { get; set; } = new();
}

public class TaskData
{
    public string Id { get; set; } = Guid.NewGuid().ToString();
    public string Title { get; set; }
}
```

And some basic CSS to style the board layout.

```css

